article.description: Oral Roberts escapes, beats Ga. Southern. 67-65
article.headline: Oral Roberts escapes, beats Ga. Southern. 67-65
article.linkText: Oral Roberts escapes, beats Ga. Southern. 67-65
article.story: CANCUN, Mexico -- Shawn Glover scored 24 points, seven in the final 1:02, as Oral Roberts squeaked by Georgia Southern 67-65 on Tuesday in the Cancun Challenge. Glover made 10 of his 18 shots for Oral Roberts (3-3) and Korey Billbury added 21, eight rebounds. Oral Roberts made one of its 14 3-pointers, but its defense forced 13 turnovers. Billbury scored 18 straight points for Oral Roberts at one point -- stretching from the 5:14 mark in the first half, until 16:29 in the second. Georgia Southern pulled within two (60-56) after two Jelani Hewitt free throws. But Oral Roberts would not relinquish its lead. Hewitt scored 19 points, grabbed seven rebounds, and had five assists to lead Georgia Southern (2-4). Curtis Diamond had 12 and Tre Bussey added 11. Oral Roberts will face Bowling Green on Wednesday, after the Falcons routed Presbyterian 67-45.
